<subSubSection id="8E8D9D164C4D150026035DB83E01EDC7" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph id="1174F1A65815C953DD9DF5D74EF65C1C" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="606C73E38043EF293D3A6A6B5C3B8693" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Easily distinguished by the strap-shaped, strongly sagittate leaves which are hirsute on both surfaces. The flowers are always solitary or paired. For a relatively slender plant the corolla is quite long reaching 3 cm. 
<emphasis id="579EF7A0BC2F41E800A2993B684C9402" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ekman</emphasis>
H8395 is an unusually robust example.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
